cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is about language modeling, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). The use of LSTM networks and character-level modeling suggests that it may fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language). The focus on neural networks and machine learning also suggests that it may fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of caching mechanisms and the creation of a new corpus suggests that it may fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of LSTM networks also suggests that it may fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the focus on language modeling and corpus construction suggests that it may fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
